So Giantt, what do you propose we do?  From what you stated so far, it appears that you are for simply going forward with the inspections and reacting accordingly.  Is that summary correct?  (I scanned this thread so forgive me if I missed something.)<P>Personally, I'm against a war with Iraq at this time.  I fully believe they are working diligently on WMDs but that's irrelevant.  I know full well that Saddam is a dicating murdering fuckhead (his sons are too).  But Saddam will not use them against us for the same reason that Russia never did.  He would probably use them against his neighbors (or his own people) but that's not really our problem.  Our dependency on oil from the middle east is down considerably.  We could easily switch to getting all our oil from countries like Canada, Russia, Mexico, Venezuela, etc.  Ultimately, I think we need to move past any dependency on oil but that's another topic altogether...<P>I also think we should pull out of Saudi Arabia, cease enforcement of the "no fly zone", drop the embargo, stop sending billions of dollars to Israel and just leave the middle east to it's own devices.  We simply don't understand those people, and they don't understand us.  (Israel has the 4th most powerful military in the world so I'm pretty sure they can take care of themselves.)  This would reduce the hatred towards the US.  They would still hate us to be sure, but probably not enough to go through all the shit they had to go through to make the 9/11 attack happen.  There will always be a mistrust and dislike between the East and the West (at least for the forseable future).  All we can do is  mitigate it's ultimate effect.<P>See, I'm an isolationist more or less.  This country gets involved with way more shit than it needs to.  We use to be isolationist and then europe pestered the shit out of us until we "got involved."  We have been involved for a long time now.  Now we act as if it's our job to do so.  We are the new face of Imperialism.  The fact that we are one of the only countries in the world capable of projecting power seems to make us think that we should.  With that power comes a greater responsibility.  Imo, it should be used only as a last resort.  <P>As for the media bias...no shit.  Well, EVERY news organization from every corner of the world has their own bias.  Every country is in it for itself.  If you think otherwise, you are extremely nieve.  Everything you read has a bias of some sort.  As human beings we are not capable of completely disengaging our emotions and beliefs from anything we do no matter how hard we try.  If you think reading foreign sources makes you wiser, then you are hitting the crack pipe a too hard.  It only makes you wiser to another country's bias.  Don't forget that a lot of the shit that goes on behind the scenes NEVER hits a newspaper.  You'd be surprised of all the bullshit that goes on that is not reported anywhere, in any country.<P>I'm not against war.  Some times shit just has to get blowed up.  But doing it based on what Iraq may do in the future with it's WMDs is a slippery slope.  Shit, we might as well just attack N. Korea and China while we're at it.  Afterall, we don't know what the fuck they will do either and we certainly know they don't like us (although they think our money is great).<P>Of course, pulling out of the middle east will piss off europe bigtime.  They are heavily dependent on middle east oil and so while they like to look at us as if we're a stupid-fuck young country that doesn't know what it's doing, they love the fact that we do it.  Fuck 'em.  Let them take care of their own bullshit for once.  <P>Giantt, while I agree with you that war isn't a good idea at this point, I guess I think your solutions are lacking, nonexistant, or simply not fully expressed?
