I'll use a quote here to illuminate a point...<P>"We're making the right decisions to end the solution" -George W. Bush<P>What you need to do is not proceed with the war.  Proceeding with the war is NOT a solution.  Other solutions need to be sought and may also be discredited but the point of individuals like giantt posting is NOT to propose we do nothing, or to propose alternate ideas...but to assert that the idea in question will impact us negatively.<P>Personally, I think there is plenty we can do to ease the situation in the Middle East.  You have to deal with things that affect the situation there..that breed terror and fundamentalists as well as annihilate situations that give credence and authority to dictators like Saddam.<P>First of all you have to deal with the Palestinean/Israeli conflict on a hardline level.<P>How?  I'll tell you.<P>1. Return to the 1967 borders.  Remove Israeli settlers from the Palestinean territories.  Share Jeruselum between Israelies and Palestineans.  Remove BOTH Arafat and Sharon from power as well as George Bush.<P>Then there is more you can do<P>2. Rearrange the relationships we have with nations in the region including Saudi Arabia.  <P>3. Establish an International Criminal Court in which has as many countries as possible including the US.<P>4. Offer more support for the United Nations and increase information gathering abilities between nations and groups.<P>5. Reorganize organizations at home such as the INS that is currently headed by a jackass (an ex Paine Webber employee).<P>6. Respect international law and attempt to stimulate the industrial growth/quality of life of countries in the middle east rather than imposing sanctions and attempting military solutions.  People will respond to the possibility of changing their lives for the better than threats against their lives and neighbors.<P>There is more you can do but all of the plans are LONG TERM oriented rather than short term and MUCH less expensive than short term military offensives presented by the Bush Administration.<P>That is what you do IMO.
