e facts] and I argue that might makes problems.  Everyone is looking to solve a problem with NO END GAME...TERROR DOESN'T END..with wars on soveriegn nations (rather than terrorist cells) that perpetuate terror.  It's expensive/costly both in lives and money.  It won't benefit the United States.<P>What we need are long term solutions that alleviate the problems in the middle east.  Not through Bush style drive by nation building and military action against the will of the international community.
